Introduction:
Docker is a platform that allows developers to package applications along with their dependencies into containers, 
which can run consistently across different environments.

Note: Docker Desktop contains Docker Desktop and its CLI.

Image vs container:
A Docker image is a read-only template contains OS, app code while a container is a running instance of that image.
Container is a machine which is used to run image.

Image is a class and container is a object.
A single image can support many containers.

