Docker hub is a place where it store its images.

"docker run -it ubuntu" is a command which is used to run container with OS ubuntu. "-it" means "interactive" => remains in same container don't exit.
"docker container ls -a" lists all containers
"docker images" lists all images
"docker start [name_of_container]" start specific container
"docker stop [name_of_container]" stop specific container
"docker exec [name_of_container] [command]" starts container with command

"docker run -it -p 1025:1025 mail"
-p => port mapping from container to local machine
1st 1025 is local pc port and second port is container port

How to create image?
1. go to hub.docker.com
2. create repo
3. in terminal run "docker build -t <username/repo_name> ."
4. in cmd run "docker push <username/repo_name>"
